                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/12.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Miller</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 18. Make earnest protest in case any attempt is made to extort
                    forced loans from American citizens. Keep the Department informed on the
                    subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
